SIMPLE: expanding
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expanding
<hw>Ex*pand"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>That expands, or may be
expanded; extending; spreading; enlarging.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Expanding bit</b></col>, <col><b>Expanding
drill</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Mech.)</fld>, <cd>a bit or drill made
adjustable for holes of various sizes; one which can be expanded in
diameter while boring.</cd> -- <col><b>Expanding pulley</b></col>
<fld>(Mach.)</fld>, <cd>a pulley so made, as in sections, that its
diameter can be increased or diminished.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expanse</ent>⟦br⟧
